1 AN ACT concerning education; relating to the national guard; permitting
2 guard members to transfer unused tuition assistance benefits from the
3 Kansas national guard educational assistance act to an eligible
4 dependent; including doctoral and professional degrees in the Kansas
5 national guard educational master's for enhanced readiness and global
6 excellence (EMERGE) program; amending K.S.A. 74-32,145, 74-
7 32,146, 74-32,147 and 74-32,148 and K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-32,149,
8 74-32,305, 74-32,306, 74-32,308 and 74-32,309 and repealing the
9 existing sections.
10
11 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
12 Section 1. K.S.A. 74-32,145 is hereby amended to read as follows:
13 74-32,145. K.S.A. 74-32,145 through 74-32,149, and amendments thereto,
14 shall be known and may be cited as the Kansas national guard educational
15 assistance act. It is the purpose of the Kansas national guard educational
16 assistance act to establish an educational assistance program under which
17 payment of the tuition and fees charged to eligible members of the Kansas
18 national guard or an eligible dependent of such guard members for
19 enrollment at Kansas educational institutions shall be provided for by the
20 state.
21 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 74-32,146 is hereby amended to read as follows: 74-
22 32,146. As used in the Kansas national guard educational assistance act:
23 (a) "Kansas educational institution" means and includes community
24 colleges, the municipal university, state educational institutions, technical
25 colleges, the institute of technology at Washburn university and accredited
26 independent institutions.
27 (b) "Eligible guard member" means any current member of the
28 Kansas national guard who is enrolled at a Kansas educational institution
29 and who is not under a suspension of favorable action flag or currently on
30 the unit unfavorable information file. The term eligible guard member
31 does not include within its meaning any member of the Kansas national
32 guard who is the holder of a baccalaureate or higher academic degree, or
33 who does not hold a high school diploma or general educational
34 development (GED) credentials.
35 (c) "Kansas national guard educational assistance program" or

HB 2185 2
1 "program" means the program established pursuant to the provisions of the
2 Kansas national guard educational assistance act.
3 (d) "Educational program" means a program which that is offered and
4 maintained by a Kansas educational institution and leads to the award of a
5 certificate, diploma or degree upon satisfactory completion of course work
6 requirements.
7 (e) "Dependent" means an individual who is registered as an eligible
8 dependent of the sponsoring eligible guard member in the defense
9 enrollment eligibility reporting system (DEERS).
10 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 74-32,147 is hereby amended to read as follows: 74-
11 32,147. The state board of regents shall adopt rules and regulations for the
12 administration of the Kansas national guard educational assistance act and
13 shall:
14 (a) Establish a mechanism to ensure distribution of funds for tuition
15 and fee reimbursement to Kansas educational institutions;
16 (b) enter into a cooperative relationship with the adjutant general to
17 ensure efficient operation of the program;
18 (c) develop and effectuate a system of accountability for all
19 disbursements under the program and provide written reports as
20 prescribed; and
21 (d) coordinate with the adjutant general a procedure to ensure initial
22 and on-going ongoing eligibility of all guard members and dependents
23 who are program participants.
24 Sec. 4. K.S.A. 74-32,148 is hereby amended to read as follows: 74-
25 32,148. (a) Subject to the availability of appropriations for the Kansas
26 national guard educational assistance program and within the limits of any
27 such appropriations, every eligible guard member or dependent who is
28 enrolled at a Kansas educational institution and who is participating in the
29 program shall receive assistance each semester in an amount equal to the
30 tuition and required fees for not more than 15 credit hours. The aggregate
31 number of credit hours for which assistance may be provided under the
32 program shall not exceed 150% of the total credit hours required for the
33 eligible guard member or dependent to complete such member's or such
34 dependent's educational program.
35 (b) Eligible guard members may either personally participate or
36 sponsor a dependent to participate in the Kansas national guard
37 educational assistance program. Assistance available to such dependent
38 under the program is subject to the availability of funds after educational
39 benefits are fully funded for all eligible guard members participating in
40 the Kansas national guard educational assistance program.
41 (b)(c) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (a), eligible guard
42 members shall not be paid the amount of tuition and required fees charged
43 for any course repeated or taken in excess of the requirements for

HB 2185 3
1 completion of the educational program in which the eligible guard member
2 or dependent is enrolled. The amount of tuition and required fees paid an
3 eligible guard member or dependent pursuant to subsection (a) shall be at
4 a rate not to exceed the maximum rate that would be charged by a state
5 educational institution, as defined in K.S.A. 76-711, and amendments
6 thereto, for enrollment of the eligible guard member or dependent.
7 (c)(d) Amounts of assistance for which an eligible guard member or
8 dependent is eligible to receive under this act shall be offset by the
9 aggregate amount of federal financial assistance received by such guard
10 member or dependent, as a result of active national guard membership, to
11 pay the costs of tuition and fees for enrollment at Kansas educational
12 institutions.
13 Sec. 5. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-32,149 is hereby amended to read as
14 follows: 74-32,149. (a) (1) In order for a member of the national guard or
15 a dependent to qualify for participation in the Kansas national guard
16 educational assistance program, an eligible guard member must shall
17 agree, in writing, to complete such member's current service obligation in
18 the Kansas national guard and serve actively in good standing with the
19 Kansas national guard for not less than 24 months upon completion of the
20 last semester for which the member or dependent receives assistance under
21 the program.
22 (2) In order for a member of the national guard to qualify for
23 assistance from the Kansas national guard educational assistance
24 program, an eligible guard member shall:
25 (A) Hold a high school diploma or high school equivalency
26 credential;
27 (B) be enrolled at a Kansas educational institution; and
28 (C) not hold a baccalaureate or higher academic degree.
29 (3) An eligible guard member may only sponsor one dependent to
30 participate in the Kansas national guard educational program during such
31 member's service.
32 (4) To qualify for assistance from the Kansas national guard
33 educational assistance program, a dependent shall:
34 (A) Hold a high school diploma or high school equivalency
35 credential;
36 (B) be enrolled at a Kansas educational institution;
37 (C) not hold a baccalaureate or higher academic degree; and
38 (D) complete and submit the Kansas student aid application with the
39 state board of regents.
40 (2)(5) Prior to becoming eligible for participation in the program,
41 each eligible guard member or dependent shall submit the free application
42 for federal student aid, and apply for any other federal tuition assistance
43 that such member or dependent also may be eligible to receive.

HB 2185 4
1 (b) In order to remain eligible for participation in the program, an
2 eligible guard member must or dependent shall remain in good standing at
3 the Kansas educational institution where enrolled, make satisfactory
4 progress toward completion of the requirements of the educational
5 program in which enrolled, and maintain a grade point average of not less
6 than 2.0 and. The eligible guard member shall maintain satisfactory
7 participation in the Kansas national guard. It shall be the responsibility of
8 the eligible guard member to obtain a certificate from the member's
9 commanding officer attesting to the member's satisfactory participation in
10 the Kansas national guard and to present the certificate to the educational
11 institution, in order to obtain a payment under this act. The certificate shall
12 be presented at the time payment is requested for completed courses. Upon
13 completion of each semester, each eligible guard member or dependent
14 receiving assistance under the program shall submit a transcript of the
15 credit hours earned by such guard member or dependent, including the
16 grades for credit hours, to such eligible member's unit of assignment.
17 (c) Upon failure of any person, who as an eligible guard member
18 received payments or whose dependent received payments under the
19 Kansas national guard educational assistance act, to satisfy the agreement
20 to continue service in the Kansas national guard as provided by subsection
21 (a)(1), such person shall pay to the state of Kansas an amount to be
22 determined as follows:
23 (1) Determine the total amount of assistance paid to such member or
24 dependent under the program;
25 (2) divide the amount determined under subsection (c)(1) by 24; and
26 (3) multiply the amount determined under subsection (c)(2) by the
27 number of months such member did not serve as required by subsection
28 (a)(1). The resulting product is the total amount of recoupment from such
29 member.
30 All amounts paid to the state under this subsection shall be deposited in
31 the state treasury and credited to the Kansas national guard educational
32 assistance program repayment fund created by K.S.A. 74-32,150, and
33 amendments thereto.
34 (d) Any eligible guard member that received payments, or whose
35 dependent received payments, under the program but has failed to satisfy
36 the agreement to continue service in the Kansas national guard as provided
37 by subsection (a)(1) by reason of extenuating circumstances or extreme
38 hardship may request a waiver from recoupment. Such request shall be in
39 writing and submitted through such member's chain of command to the
40 Kansas national guard education services office. The chief of staff of the
41 Kansas army national guard or the director of staff for the Kansas air
42 national guard shall review all requests for a waiver from recoupment, and
43 the decision to issue such waiver shall be made by either officer as such

