1 officer deems appropriate.
2 Sec. 6. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-32,305 is hereby amended to read as
3 follows: 74-32,305. (a) K.S.A. 74-32,305 through 74-32,310, and
4 amendments thereto, shall be known and may be cited as the Kansas
5 national guard educational master's for enhanced readiness and global
6 excellence (EMERGE) program.
7 (b) The purpose of the Kansas national guard EMERGE program is to
8 establish a master's an advanced degree assistance program under which
9 payment of the tuition and fees charged to eligible members of the Kansas
10 national guard for enrollment in master's advanced degree programs at
11 Kansas educational institutions shall be provided by the state pursuant to
12 the EMERGE program.
13 Sec. 7. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-32,306 is hereby amended to read as
14 follows: 74-32,306. As used in the Kansas national guard educational
15 master's for enhanced readiness and global excellence (EMERGE)
16 program:
17 (a) "Educational programAdvanced degree" means a master's degree
18 program offered or maintained by a Kansas educational institution that
19 leads to the award of a master's, professional degree or doctorate awarded
20 to an eligible guard member upon satisfactory completion of the course
21 work requirements of such degree program offered or maintained by a
22 Kansas educational institution.
23 (b) "Doctorate" means a degree requiring three or more academic
24 years of full-time academic study or the equivalent in part-time attendance
25 that follows the successful completion of a baccalaureate or master's
26 degree. A "doctorate" may be either a research or a professional practice
27 degree.
28 (c) "Eligible guard member" means any member of the Kansas
29 national guard who has been accepted into an eligible master's advanced
30 degree program and who is not under a suspension of favorable flag action
31 or on the unit unfavorable information file. "Eligible guard member"
32 includes nonconcurrent guard members accepted into an eligible
33 professional degree program if they are qualified to join the Kansas
34 national guard.
35 (c)(d) "Kansas educational institution" means a state educational
36 institution, as defined in K.S.A. 76-711, and amendments thereto,
37 Washburn university or an accredited independent institution, as defined in
38 K.S.A. 72-3222, and amendments thereto.
39 (d)(e) "Kansas national guard educational master's for enhanced
40 readiness and global excellence program" or "EMERGE program" means
41 the program established pursuant to the provisions of the Kansas national
42 guard educational master's for enhanced readiness and global excellence
43 program.

HB 2185 6
1 (f) "Master's degree" means a degree requiring not less than one year
2 of academic work or the equivalent in part-time attendance and follows
3 the successful completion of a baccalaureate degree.
4 (g) "Professional degree" means a degree that requires not less than
5 three years of full-time study or the equivalent in part-time attendance that
6 follows the successful completion of a baccalaureate degree, such as a
7 juris doctor degree or a physician's assistant degree.
8 Sec. 8. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-32,308 is hereby amended to read as
9 follows: 74-32,308. (a) Subject to the availability of appropriations for the
10 Kansas national guard EMERGE program and within the limits of any
11 such appropriations, except as provided in subsections (b) and (c), every
12 eligible national guard member who is enrolled at a Kansas educational
13 institution and participating in the program shall receive assistance each
14 semester in an amount equal to the tuition and required fees for not more
15 than 15 hours. The aggregate number of credit hours for which assistance
16 may be provided under the program shall not exceed 150% of the total
17 credit hours required for the eligible guard member to complete such
18 member's master's advanced degree program.
19 (b) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (a), eligible guard
20 members shall not be paid the amount of tuition and fees charged for any
21 course repeated or taken in excess of the requirements for completion of
22 the master's advanced degree program in which the eligible guard member
23 is enrolled. The amount of tuition and required fees paid an eligible guard
24 member pursuant to subsection (a) shall be at a rate not to exceed the
25 maximum rate that would be charged by a state educational institution for
26 enrollment of the eligible guard member.
27 (c) Amounts of assistance for which an eligible guard member is
28 eligible to receive under this act shall be offset by the aggregate amount of
29 federal or institutional tuition assistance received by such eligible guard
30 member, as a result of active national guard membership, to pay costs of
31 tuition and fees for enrollment at Kansas educational institutions.
32 Sec. 9. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 74-32,309 is hereby amended to read as
33 follows: 74-32,309. (a) On or before July 1 of each academic year, The
34 adjutant general shall select up to 100 eligible national guard members
35 annually who applied to the program to receive assistance from such
36 program. The number of eligible guard members in the program shall not
37 exceed 200 eligible guard members in any one school year.
38 (b) (1) In order to qualify for participation in the Kansas national
39 guard EMERGE program, an eligible national guard member shall agree,
40 in writing, to complete such member's current service obligation in the
41 Kansas national guard and serve actively in good standing with the Kansas
42 national guard or in a duty status affiliated with the Kansas national guard
43 for not less than 48 months upon completion of the last semester for which

HB 2185 7
1 the member receives assistance under the program for a master's degree
2 and for not less than 72 months upon graduation for a doctorate or
3 professional degree for which the member receives assistance under the
4 program.
5 (2) Prior to becoming eligible for participation in the program, each
6 eligible guard member shall submit the free application for federal student
7 aid and apply for any other federal tuition assistance that such member
8 also may be eligible to receive.
9 (c) In order to remain eligible for participation in the program, an
10 eligible guard member shall remain in good standing at the Kansas
11 educational institution where such member is enrolled, make satisfactory
12 progress toward completion of the requirements of such member's master's
13 advanced degree program, maintain a grade point average of not less than
14 2.75 for a master's degree or a 3.0 for a doctorate or professional degree
15 and maintain satisfactory participation in the Kansas national guard.
16 (d) (1) Upon failure of any eligible guard member who received
17 payments under the Kansas national guard EMERGE program to satisfy
18 the agreement to continue service in the Kansas national guard as provided
19 by subsection (a), such person shall pay to the state of Kansas an amount
20 to be determined as follows:
21 (A) Determine the total amount of assistance paid to such member
22 under the program;
23 (B) divide the amount determined under subsection (d)(1)(A) by 48
24 for a master's degree or 72 for a doctorate or professional degree; and
25 (C) multiply the amount determined under subsection (d)(1)(B) by
26 the number of months such member did not serve as required by
27 subsection (a). The resulting product is the total amount of recoupment to
28 be paid by such member.
29 (2) All amounts paid to the state under this subsection shall be
30 deposited in the state treasury and credited to the Kansas national guard
31 EMERGE program repayment fund created by section 6 K.S.A. 2024
32 Supp. 74-32,310, and amendments thereto.
33 (e) Any eligible guard member that received payments under the
34 program but has failed to satisfy the agreement to continue service in the
35 Kansas national guard as provided by subsection (a) by reason of
36 extenuating circumstances or extreme hardship may request a waiver from
37 recoupment under subsection (d). Such request shall be in writing and
38 submitted through such member's chain of command to the Kansas
39 national guard education services office. The chief of staff of the Kansas
40 army national guard or the director of staff for the Kansas air national
41 guard shall review all requests for a waiver from recoupment, and the
42 decision to issue such waiver shall be made by either officer as such
43 officer deems appropriate.

